# Kubernetes YAML Files Repository

## üìå Overview
This repository contains commonly used **Kubernetes YAML configuration files** for deploying, managing, and operating containerized applications in a Kubernetes cluster.

These files cover core Kubernetes objects such as Pods, Deployments, Services, ConfigMaps, Secrets, Volumes, Jobs, CronJobs, StatefulSets, and Ingress.

This repository is useful for:
- Kubernetes learning and practice
- Interview preparation
- Real-time DevOps projects
- Reference for YAML syntax and structure

---

## üìÇ Repository Structure

| File Name | Description |
|---------|------------|
| `pod.yaml` | Defines a single Pod to run a container |
| `deployment.yaml` | Manages application replicas and rolling updates |
| `service.yaml` | Exposes Pods internally or externally |
| `configmap.yaml` | Stores non-sensitive configuration data |
| `secrets.yaml` | Stores sensitive data like passwords and tokens |
| `pv.yaml` | Defines Persistent Volume (storage resource) |
| `pvc.yaml` | Requests storage from Persistent Volume |
| `statefulset.yaml` | Manages stateful applications |
| `job.yaml` | Runs a one-time batch job |
| `cronjob.yaml` | Runs scheduled jobs |
| `ingress.yaml` | Manages external HTTP/HTTPS access |

